    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Embroidery technique employing metal threads fixed to a fabric. The threads consist of cotton or silk coated in metals such as imitation gold, silver and copper. The technique originated in Asia some two thousand years ago.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
